<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; DT 466E, DT 466, 530, 530E, and HT 530 Diesel Engines - Rocker Arm Assembly, Camshaft
        Assembly, Tappets, and Push Rods - Clean, Inspect, Measure, and Test - Inspect and Measure Camshaft Bushings
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s210010503.5" svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Inspect and Measure Camshaft Bushings</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect four camshaft bushings for wear and proper running clearance.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure camshaft bushing journal outside diameter at two locations, 90&#176; apart with
                <hotlnk document="eges2101_X2100504.xml" xrefid="t210010504">Outside Micrometer</hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure camshaft bushing inside diameter with bushing installed in crankcase. Use
                <hotlnk document="eges2101_X2100504.xml" xrefid="t210010504">Telescoping Gauge</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk document="eges2101_X2100504.xml" xrefid="t210010504">Outside Micrometer</hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Subtract readings obtained in Steps 2 and 3 to determine running clearance.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If maximum allowable running clearance in "
                <hotlnk xrefid="t21001501">Specifications</hotlnk>
                " is exceeded, replace camshaft bushings. See "Remove Camshaft Bushings" in this section.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>When servicing camshaft bushings, crankshaft and main bearings must be removed from crankcase to
                    avoid debris contamination.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
